{{nihongo|''' Kōchō'''|弘長|}} was a {{nihongo|[[Japanese era name]]|年号,|''nengō'',|lit. "year name"}} after ''[[Bun'ō]]'' and before ''[[Bun'ei]].''  This period spanned the years from February 1261 to February 1264.<ref>Nussbaum, Louis-Frédéric. (2005). "''Kōchō''" in {{Google books|p2QnPijAEmEC|''Japan Encyclopedia'', p. 539|page=539}}; n.b., Louis-Frédéric is pseudonym of Louis-Frédéric Nussbaum, ''see'' [http://dispatch.opac.ddb.de/DB=4.1/PPN?PPN=128842709 Deutsche Nationalbibliothek Authority File] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20120524174828/http://dispatch.opac.ddb.de/DB=4.1/PPN?PPN=128842709 |date=2012-05-24 }}.</ref> The reigning emperor was {{nihongo|[[Emperor Kameyama|Kameyama]]''-tennō''|亀山天皇}}.<ref>Titsingh, Isaac. (1834). ''Annales des empereurs du Japon'', pp. 255-261; Varley, H. Paul. (1980). ''Jinnō Shōtōki.'' p. 232-233.</ref>

==Change of era==
* {{nihongo|''''' Kōchō gannen'''''|弘長元年}}; 1261: The new era name was created to mark an event or a number of events. The previous era ended and a new one commenced in ''Bun'ō'' 2.

==Events of the '' Kōchō'' era==
* '''June 11, 1261''' (''Kōchō 1, 12th day of the 5th month'')<!-- NengoCalc  
弘長一年五月十二日 -->: Nichiren was exiled to Itō in Izu.<ref name="n47">Nichren. (2004). ''Writings of Nichiren Shonin: Doctrine 3'', p. 47.</ref>
* '''March 19, 1262''' (''Kōchō 2, 28th day of the 11th month'')<!-- NengoCalc 弘長二年二月二十八日 -->: Shinran passes away at the age of 90
* '''April 1, 1263''' (''Kōchō 3, 22nd day of the 2nd month'')<!-- NengoCalc  弘長三年二月二十二日 -->: Nichiren was pardoned.<ref name="n47"/>

